<section>
	<title>User Workspace</title>
	<section>
		<title>Open the User Workspace</title>
	</section>
	<itemizedlist>
		<listitem>
			User Workspace
			<emphasis role="bold">is the specific space that helps you access
				and perform all administration actions. After your account is
				authenticated, you will see an arrow on the left. Click on this
				arrow to open the</emphasis>
			User Workspace:
		</listitem>
	</itemizedlist>
	<mediaobject>
		<imageobject>
			<imagedata fileref="images/UserWorkspace1.png" format="PNG"></imagedata>
		</imageobject>
	</mediaobject>
	<section>
		<title>User Workspace</title>
	</section>
	<mediaobject>
		<imageobject>
			<imagedata fileref="images/OpenUserWorkspace1.png" format="PNG"></imagedata>
		</imageobject>
	</mediaobject>
	<para>
		In the User Workspace, you can easily add, edit and remove Gadgets.
		See more details on how to take that actions in
		<link linkend="Portal:Manage Gadgets in User Workspace">Portal:Manage Gadgets in User
			Workspace</link>
		.
	</para>
	<section>
		<title>*Administration* in the *User Workspace*</title>
	</section>
	<para>
		Go to
		<emphasis role="bold">GateIn Start</emphasis>
		-&gt; <emphasis role="bold">Administration</emphasis>. You can see as the below screenshot:</para><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/Administration2.png" format="PNG"></imagedata></imageobject></mediaobject>
<section><title>*Page Navigations* in the *User Workspace*</title></section>
<para>Go to <emphasis role="bold">GateIn Start</emphasis> -&gt; <emphasis role="bold">Page Navigations</emphasis>. Users can easily see and access pages in GateIn Portal.</para><mediaobject><imageobject><imagedata fileref="images/PageNavigation.png" format="PNG"></imagedata></imageobject></mediaobject>
<section><title>Who can access the User Workspace ?</title></section>
<para>Please refer to <link linkend="User Workspace Configuration">User Workspace Configuration</link> for more details on who can access and perform all administration actions in the <emphasis role="bold">User Workspace</emphasis>.</para>
</section>